"(1) (i) , a local observer, arrived at the secure counting facility in just before dusk, drawn by the hum of activity and the tense anticipation that hung in the air. As he entered, the fluorescent lights cast a sterile glow over rows of ballot boxes, each sealed with official indelible stamps. The room buzzed with the quiet urgency of officials and volunteers, their faces illuminated by screens displaying preliminary tallies. Owen Thomas. witnessed a vote counting disruption.\n(2) Owen felt a prick of anxiety; this was the moment when the will of the people would be made manifest, and any disruption could have far-reaching consequences. (i) Suddenly, a sharp commotion erupted near the central counting table. September 27, 2025.\n(3) A group of staff rushed past, their expressions shifting from calm professionalism to confusion as an official’s announcement crackled through the room: “There’s been an irregularity in the ballots for Ward 12.” Owen’s senses sharpened—he could hear the shuffle of feet, the muffled voices of workers debating, and the clink of metal trays being moved. The orderly rhythm of counting was shattered, replaced by a rising tension that seemed to thicken the air.\n(4) (i) Owen moved closer, careful not to draw attention, but the disruption was clear: a stack of ballots had been separated from its corresponding tally sheet, and several sheets bore mismatched serial numbers. A senior counting officer barked instructions, and two teams sprang into action—one to re-examine the ballots, the other to cross-reference the records on a laptop. Nairobi County.\n(5) Owen watched as the room’s energy shifted from nervous anticipation to focused determination, the clock’s hands ticking toward midnight. (i)"